	<sect1 id="text-editor">
		<title>Text Editor</title>
		<para>
			To enable the &project; plugin in <command>gedit</command> choose
			<menuchoice>
				<guimenu>Edit</guimenu>
				<guimenuitem>Preferences</guimenuitem>
			</menuchoice>
			.  Then select the tab <guilabel>Plugin</guilabel> and check <guilabel>Text 
			Encryption</guilabel>.
		</para>
		<sect2 id="encrypt-te">
			<title>Encrypt Text</title>
			<para>
				To encrypt a selection of text, select the text you want to encrypt and 
				choose
				<menuchoice>
					<guimenu>Edit</guimenu>
					<guimenuitem>Encrypt</guimenuitem>
				</menuchoice>
				.  You will then be presented with a dialog containing a list of 
				recipients.  Check the boxes next to the people you want to encrypt text 
				to and press <guilabel>Ok</guilabel>. You can now copy or save the 
				encrypted text.
			</para>
		</sect2>
		<sect2 id="sign-te">
			<title>Sign Text</title>
			<para>
				To sign a selection of text, select the text you want to sign and 
				choose
				<menuchoice>
					<guimenu>Edit</guimenu>
					<guimenuitem>Sign</guimenuitem>
				</menuchoice>
				.  You will then be prompted for the passphrase to your secret key. 	
				After entering your passphrase you will be able copy or save the 
				signed text.
			</para>
		</sect2>
		<sect2 id="decrypt/verify-te">
			<title>Decrypt/Verify Text</title>
			<para>
				To Decrypt and or Verify a selection of text, select the text you want 
				to sign and choose
				<menuchoice>
					<guimenu>Edit</guimenu>
					<guimenuitem>Decrypt/Verify</guimenuitem>
				</menuchoice>
				.  If you are decrypting text, you will then be prompted for the 
				passphrase to your secret key. 	After entering your passphrase you
				 will be able copy or save the decrypted text.
			</para>
		</sect2>
	</sect1>
